  "text": "Signature-Based: IDS like SNORT uses sets of signatures to determine if an event is malicious or not [CITATION_1] . The comparison could be based on simple features such as header of an email address, the sender's domain name or more complicated such as comparing an email with the blacklisted domains or known malicious activities. Of course this technique is vulnerable to zero-day attacks [CITATION_2] as signatures will not be available in the database.",
